<p class="">I did not suggest the right hon. Gentleman was indifferent to the hardship. What I did say was that, while his statement that any such marriage allowance was higher than immediately before the war was accurate in the terms in which it was stated, it gave a cruelly wrong impression as to the changes in the reliefs.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
